      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "Thursday morning a party of II\ninterested in irrigation matters\nwill start over the Northern Pacific\nfor Albuquerque, n. NJ, to attend\nthe national irrigation congress,\nSeptember 20 to October g. and\nbring back the meeting for next\nyear to Spokane. The party will\ninclude Laclan Mclean, ]. Grier\nLong, w. G. Malloy, r. A. Hutchin-\nson. ]. d. Valentine. Arthur Hook\ner, Levi G. Monroe and possibly\nID. T. Ham and Walter Z. Lee. The\nlatter two will probably go, but to-\nday have not made up their minds\nfor sure. Levi G. Monroe, secre-\ntary of the chamber of commerce.\nwill deliver an address on Eastern\nWashington\" before the congress.\n\n\nReturning the entire party may\ngo to San Francisco to attend the\nnational meeting of commercial\nclubs which opens there October 5.\nThis move is not certain yet. Sec\nrotary Monroe will go there in any\nevent."
    }
  ]
